2) soil <BR> 1d) (in phrases) <BR> 1d1) people of the land <BR> 1d2) space or distance of country (in measurements of distance) <BR> 1d3) level or plain country <BR> 1d4) land of the living <BR> 1d5) end(s) of the earth <BR> 1e) (almost wholly late in usage) <BR> 1e1) lands, countries <BR> 1e1a) often in contrast to Canaan"}}], :versions=>[{:version=>"New International Version", :text=>"and also seven pairs of every kind of bird, male and female, to keep their various kinds alive throughout the earth."}, {:version=>"New Living Translation", :text=>"Also take seven pairs of every kind of bird. There must be a male and a female in each pair to ensure that all life will survive on the earth after the flood."}, {:version=>"English Standard Version", :text=>"and seven pairs of the birds of the heavens also, male and female, to keep their offspring alive on the face of all the earth."}, {:version=>"Berean Study Bible", :text=>"and seven pairs of every kind of bird of the air, male and female, to preserve their offspring on the face of all the earth."}, {:version=>"New American Standard Bible ", :text=>"also of the birds of the sky, by sevens, male and female, to keep offspring alive on the face of all the earth."}, {:version=>"New King James Version", :text=>"also seven each of birds of the air, male and female, to keep the species alive on the face of all the earth."}, {:version=>"King James Bible", :text=>"Of fowls also of the air by sevens, the male and the female; to keep seed alive upon the face of all the earth."}, {:version=>"Christian Standard Bible", :text=>"and seven pairs, male and female, of the birds of the sky--in order to keep offspring alive throughout the earth."}, {:version=>"Contemporary English Version", :text=>"Also take seven pairs of every kind of bird with you. Do this so there will always be animals and birds on the earth. "}, {:version=>"Good News Translation", :text=>"Take also seven pairs of each kind of bird. Do this so that every kind of animal and bird will be kept alive to reproduce again on the earth. "}, {:version=>"Holman Christian Standard Bible", :text=>"and seven pairs, male and female, of the birds of the sky--in order to keep offspring alive on the face of the whole earth. "}, {:version=>"International Standard Version", :text=>"along with seven pairs of the flying birds, male and female, in order to keep their offspring alive on the surface of all the earth. "}, {:version=>"NET Bible", :text=>"and also seven of every kind of bird in the sky, male and female, to preserve their offspring on the face of the earth."}, {:version=>"New Heart English Bible", :text=>"Also of the clean flying creatures of the sky, seven pairs, a male and a female, and of all the unclean flying creatures, one pair, a male and a female, to preserve their offspring on the surface of all the earth."}, {:version=>"GOD'S WORD® Translation", :text=>"Also, take seven pairs of every kind of bird (a male and a female of each) to preserve animal life all over the earth after the flood."}, {:version=>"JPS Tanakh 1917", :text=>"of the fowl also of the air, seven and seven, male and female; to keep seed alive upon the face of all the earth."}, {:version=>"New American Standard 1977 ", :text=>"also of the birds of the sky, by sevens, male and female, to keep offspring alive on the face of all the earth."}, {:version=>"King James 2000 Bible", :text=>"Of fowls also of the air by sevens, the male and the female; to keep their kind alive upon the face of all the earth."}, {:version=>"American King James Version", :text=>"Of fowls also of the air by sevens, the male and the female; to keep seed alive on the face of all the earth."}, {:version=>"American Standard Version", :text=>"of the birds also of the heavens, seven and seven, male and female, to keep seed alive upon the face of all the earth."}, {:version=>"Brenton Septuagint Translation", :text=>"And of clean flying creatures of the sky sevens, male and female, and of all unclean flying creatures pairs, male and female, to maintain seed on all the earth."}, {:version=>"Douay-Rheims Bible", :text=>"But of the beasts that are unclean two and two, the male and female. Of the fowls also of the air seven and seven,the male and the female: that seed may be saved upon the face of the whole earth. "}, {:version=>"Darby Bible Translation", :text=>"Also of the fowl of the heavens by sevens, male and female; to keep seed alive on the face of all the earth."}, {:version=>"English Revised Version", :text=>"of the fowl also of the air, seven and seven, male and female: to keep seed alive upon the face of all the earth."}, {:version=>"Webster's Bible Translation", :text=>"Of fowls of the air also by sevens, the male and the female; to keep seed alive on the face of all the earth."}, {:version=>"World English Bible", :text=>"Also of the birds of the sky, seven and seven, male and female, to keep seed alive on the surface of all the earth."}, {:version=>"Young's Literal Translation", :text=>" also, of fowl of the heavens seven pairs, a male and a female, to keep alive seed on the face of all the earth;"}]}